<doc>
  <member name="EMRPOLYDRAW">
    <summary>
      <para>The <b>EMRPOLYDRAW</b> structure contains members for the <see cref="PolyDraw" /> enhanced metafile record.</para>
    </summary>
    <seealso cref="EMR" />
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/gdi/metafile-structures">Metafile Structures</seealso>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/gdi/metafiles">Metafiles Overview</seealso>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//previous-versions/dd162807(v=vs.85)">POINTL</seealso>
    <seealso cref="PolyDraw" />
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//previous-versions/dd162907(v=vs.85)">RECTL</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="EMRPOLYDRAW.emr">
    <summary>
      <para>The base structure for all record types.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="EMRPOLYDRAW.rclBounds">
    <summary>
      <para>The bounding rectangle, in device units.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="EMRPOLYDRAW.cptl">
    <summary>
      <para>The number of points.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="EMRPOLYDRAW.aptl">
    <summary>
      <para>An array of <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//previous-versions/dd162807(v=vs.85)">POINTL</a> structures, representing the data points in logical units.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="EMRPOLYDRAW.abTypes">
    <summary>
      <para>An array of values that specifies how each point in the <b>aptl</b> array is used. Each element can be one of the following values: PT_MOVETO, PT_LINETO, or PT_BEZIERTO. The PT_LINETO or PT_BEZIERTO value can be combined with the PT_CLOSEFIGURE value using the bitwise-OR operator.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>